# Requirements — `<feature-slug>`

**EARS notation only.** Every line must match one of the 5 patterns. Linted by `scripts/ears-lint.py`.

The 5 EARS patterns (Mavin et al., IEEE RE'09):

| Pattern | Template |
|---|---|
| **Ubiquitous** | `REQ-NNN: The <system> shall <response>.` |
| **Event-driven** | `REQ-NNN: When <trigger>, the <system> shall <response>.` |
| **State-driven** | `REQ-NNN: While <precondition>, the <system> shall <response>.` |
| **Optional** | `REQ-NNN: Where <feature included>, the <system> shall <response>.` |
| **Unwanted behaviour** | `REQ-NNN: If <trigger>, then the <system> shall <response>.` |

Every REQ-NNN must have a unique 3+ digit number. No prose paragraphs, no "should be", no TODO/TBD/FIXME/various/etc.

---

## Functional requirements

REQ-001: The system shall persist user registrations in the users table.

REQ-002: When a user submits valid registration JSON to POST /auth/register, the system shall return 201 with the stored user record.

REQ-003: If the registration JSON fails JSON Schema validation, then the system shall return 422 with a per-field error list.

REQ-004: While a user is in the unverified state, the system shall reject all requests to /api/* with 403 unverified.

REQ-005: Where the optional 2FA feature is enabled, the registration response shall include a TOTP enrollment URL.

## Non-functional requirements

REQ-100: The system shall complete user registration in less than 500ms p99.

REQ-101: The system shall accept registrations at a sustained rate of 100 req/sec without degradation.
